article.headline: Fresno State 67, San Jose State 64
article.story: FRESNO, Calif. (AP) -- Quinton Hosley scored 17 points and Dominic McGuire added 15 to help Fresno State defeat San Jose State 67-64 on Monday night. McGuire, who also posted 13 rebounds and five blocks, made one of two free throws with 1:08 left to put the Bulldogs ahead 65-59 before San Jose State rallied to within a point. Menelik Barbary led the Spartans with 16 points, including a two-handed dunk that trimmed Fresno State's lead to 65-64 with 47.6 seconds left. Barbary also had 12 rebounds. In the wild sequence that followed, Barbary blocked McGuire's dunk attempt before getting his own dunk blocked from behind by Fresno State's Eddie Miller. McGuire hit two free throws with 16.8 seconds remaining to seal the victory for Fresno State (14-5 overall, 3-3 Western Athletic Conference), which snapped a three-game losing streak. San Jose State (2-16, 1-5) had a chance to tie the game, but Carlton Spencer missed an off-balance 3-pointer at the buzzer. Miller and Hector Hernandez added 12 points each for Fresno State, which overcame 39.3 percent shooting from the field. All of Miller's points came on 3-pointers. San Jose State led for most of the game until McGuire's baseline drive with 7:04 to go put Fresno State ahead for good, despite a late surge by the Spartans that included five points by Hill. San Jose State led by as many as nine points in the first half before Miller's 3-pointer sparked a 10-2 Fresno State run to close the gap to 34-30 at the intermission. The Spartans shot 48.3 percent in the first half thanks to a patient half-court offense that created numerous shots in the lane. Spencer contributed 14 points, and Jamon Hill added 11.
